Bafana Bafana assistant coach Helman Mkhalele. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Football Association has finally ended all the speculation and appointed the second Bafana Bafana assistant coach. 1996 Africa Cup of Nations champion Helman Mkhalele has joined Hugo Broos' technical team as the second assistant. Broos also brought Macedonian Cedomir Janevski who is his first deputy. READ: Sundowns vow to exploit 'weak' Ahly defence in CAF Champions League The Belgian had earlier publicly declared former national team coach Molefi Ntseki as his preferred candidate but SAFA moved to rubbish the claim before subsequent negotiations reached an impasse. The association also announced that they have secured an international friendly with Uganda on 10 June.